ğŸ‰Pika World Breakfast Market Update - 8 Nov 2023ğŸš€The tech rally continues.ğŸ¯The S&P 500 and Nasdaq are riding to their longest greens since 2021. It comes at a time when the 10-year Treasury yield fell to 4.57%  a dramatic fall from the 5% hit in October. During that period  both indices tapped into the correction territory and have since then bounced back remarkably.Last week was a period of bad news and good news. This week  there is a lack of news as a catalyst  with earnings firmly rolling in the background.ğŸ¯Helping this long rally in melody is the expectation that the Fed will pivot. However  comments from Fed officials yesterday helped tame such expectations as Fed members reinforced the idea that inflation remains too high and the possibility of a rate hike remains a possibility. Yet  traders soaked in the mood of what they wish to hear and reduce the weightage of the Fed's rhetoric.ğŸ¯A key note is that Uncle Powell will speak at 10.15 pm SG time today.
